### =========================================================================
### Express Prisma Advanced Boilerplate — API Documentation & HTTP Requests
### =========================================================================
### Designed to run with the `REST Client` extension for VS Code.
###
### 🍪 Cookie-Based Authentication (Default)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### On successful Login, the server automatically sets two HttpOnly, Secure
### cookies in your browser / REST Client cookie jar:
###   • accessToken  — short-lived JWT  (default: 15 minutes)
###   • refreshToken — long-lived JWT   (default: 7 days)
###
### These cookies are sent automatically with every subsequent request.
### You do NOT need to set the Authorization header manually if cookies
### are being sent by your HTTP client.
###
### 🔑 Bearer Token (Optional / Fallback)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### The `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header is an ALTERNATIVE auth method.
### Use it when:
###   • You are testing from a client that does not support cookies
###     (e.g. curl, mobile apps, or cross-origin REST testing tools)
###   • You explicitly want to pass the token in the header instead of a cookie
###
### Instructions:
### 1. Execute "Login" and copy the `accessToken` from the response cookie/body.
### 2. Paste it into the `@accessToken` variable below.
### 3. The Authorization header is already included on protected endpoints
###    as a fallback — remove it if your client supports cookies natively.
### =========================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@accessToken = YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken = YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

# Test User Credentials
@email = super@gmail.com
@password = Password1#
@confirmPassword = Password1#
@firstName = John
@lastName = Doe

# Verification & Recovery
@verifyEmailOtp = 123456
@resetPassToken = resetPassToken
@newPassword = NewPassword1#

### =========================================================================
### HEALTH & METRICS
### =========================================================================

### 1. Root Welcome Endpoint
# @name root
GET http://localhost:5000
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Health Check Checkup
# @name healthCheck
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Content-Type: application/json


### =========================================================================
### AUTHENTICATION MODULE
### =========================================================================

### 1. Register User (Creates unverified account and sends OTP)
# @name registerUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "{{firstName}}",
  "lastName": "{{lastName}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "confirmPassword": "{{confirmPassword}}"
}

### 2. Resend Email Verification Code (OTP)
# @name resendVerificationCode
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/resend-verification-code
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### 3. Verify Email Address (Using the 6-digit OTP sent to email)
# @name verifyEmail
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "code": "{{verifyEmailOtp}}"
}

### 4. Login User (Returns accessToken in body and cookies)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 5. Refresh Access Token (Uses HttpOnly refreshToken cookie or headers)
# @name refreshToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Logout User (Invalidates token via Redis blacklist)
# @name logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 7. Forgot Password (Initiates recovery, sends email with JWT token)
# @name forgotPassword
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### 8. Resend Forgot Password Email
# @name resendForgotPassword
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/resend-forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### 9. Reset Password (Completes recovery using reset token)
# @name resetPassword
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{resetPassToken}}",
  "newPassword": "{{newPassword}}"
}


### =========================================================================
### USER MANAGEMENT MODULE
### =========================================================================

@userId = 9b7a3fa1-6e1c-457d-872b-0b4efedb33e7
@oldPassword = SecurePass1#
@newUserPassword = NewPassword1#
@cursor = e61fea17-5eb3-4d86-881a-7ef844056722

### 1. Get All Users (Admin / Super Admin only)
# @name getAllUsers
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Get All Users - Filtered + Paginated with Offset (Admin / Super Admin only)
# @name getAllUsersFiltered
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&limit=5&sortBy=createdAt&sortOrder=desc&status=ACTIVE&createdAtFrom=2025-06-21&createdAtTo=2026-06-21
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Get All Users - Filtered + Paginated with Cursor (Admin / Super Admin only)
# @name getAllUsersCursor
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/cursor?limit=5&direction=forward&sortBy=createdAt&sortOrder=desc
# GET {{baseUrl}}/users/cursor?limit=5&cursor={{cursor}}&direction=forward&sortBy=createdAt&sortOrder=desc
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Create User Manually (Admin / Super Admin only)
# @name createUserManually
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "username": "manualuser",
  "role": "USER",
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "firstName": "{{firstName}}",
  "lastName": "{{lastName}}",
  "gender": "MALE",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

### 5. Get Own Profile (Any authenticated user)
# @name getOwnProfile
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Update Own Profile - JSON Profile Details
# @name updateOwnProfile
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "{{firstName}}",
  "lastName": "{{lastName}}",
  "phone": "+9876543210",
  "gender": "FEMALE",
  "bio": "Lead Full Stack Architect",
  "address": "San Francisco, CA",
  "dateOfBirth": "1994-04-20",
  "timezone": "America/Los_Angeles",
  "locale": "en-US"
}

### 7. Update Own Profile - Multipart Request (Profile details + optional avatar)
# @name updateOwnProfileMultipart
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="avatar"; filename="avatar.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./uploads/avatar.png
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="firstName"

Jane
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### 8. Upload / Replace Own Avatar Only (Multipart)
# @name updateOwnAvatarOnly
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me/avatar
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="avatar"; filename="avatar.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./uploads/avatar.png
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### 9. Delete Own Avatar
# @name deleteOwnAvatar
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/me/avatar
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 10. Change Own Password
# @name changeOwnPassword
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldPassword": "{{oldPassword}}",
  "newPassword": "{{newUserPassword}}"
}

### 11. Deactivate Own Account (Sets status to INACTIVE)
# @name deactivateOwnAccount
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 12. Reactivate Own Account (Sets status back to ACTIVE)
# @name reactivateOwnAccount
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me/reactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 13. Get User by ID (Admin / Super Admin only)
# @name getUserById
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 14. Update User Status (Admin / Super Admin only)
# @name updateUserStatus
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "SUSPENDED"
}

### 15. Update User Role (Super Admin only)
# @name updateUserRole
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/role
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

### 16. Soft Delete User (Admin / Super Admin only)
# @name deleteUserSoft
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 17. Hard Delete User (Super Admin only)
# @name deleteUserHard
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/hard
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
